        "ratings": [
            {
                "comment": "*English 144 not 100*\n\nKate, without a doubt, is the most kind professor I have had yet. She cares about her students just as much as her material. She is one of the reasons why I feel comfortable and optimistic about going to school at UW-Madison. If there is any advice I could give a freshman or sophomore, TAKE DR. MERZ's CLASS",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Kate is an awesome professor! She is always willing to workshop your paper with you an gives great feedback. As long as you try and participate in the class, you will get a good grade. Course load isn't too heavy.",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Kate was great. She had no problem explaining things again if they were initially confusing. She also gives great feedback on papers and assignments, and she makes class fun. She was a super easy grader; as long as you followed the instructions and put in decent effort you will likely get an A on papers. I highly recommend Kate for any class. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Dr. Merz is a very kind, helpful professor. She always does her absolute best to keep all students engaged during lectures, and I like how she makes them more discussion based and interactive. The papers can get to be a lot sometimes, but Dr. Merz leaves great feedback and is a lenient grader that wants her students to succeed. I recommend her!",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Kate was my favorite prof. this semester. She was super caring and made sure that mental health came first. Kate was very accommodating when I needed to go home for an extended amount of time and always made the classroom a comfortable place to be.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Kate was a great professor! Especially with everything being online, she was super flexible. You could talk to her about any issues and she was very helpful. We wrote quite a few papers but she offered a lot of feedback and made the topics broad so we could write about basically anything we wanted. Would definitely recommend her!",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Kate Merz was one of the nicest professors I was able to have in my freshman year of college at UW- Madison. I was in her English 100 class and I was very happy with my grade and the way she cared about how her students were feeling even outside of class. She was very respectful and was very understanding. Highly recommend!!",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Dr. Merz was one of my favorite professors during my fall semester. She is very nice and gives you good/helpful feedback on your essays. During the course, there are a ton of short readings that you are require to read before discussion and then some short writing assignments in between that are 2-3 pages along with 3 writing projects.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Kate was a very nice professor and a fair grader. There were many &quot;short&quot; stories to read throughout the semester which typically had very political topics. Don't expect to get grades back quickly. She knows that we have other things going on which makes her very understanding. I would definitely recommend if you are looking for a chill professor.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Such an amazing professor! So friendly and willing to help you achieve in the class if you ask for help. Definitely was able to make a connection even though it was online! Definitely an easy grader and reasonable with participation. I would strongly recommend taking a class with Professor Merz! It was also an easy A which is nice too!",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
